zyxelMvr.name: zyxelMvr
zyxelMvr.description: The subtree for Multicast VLAN Registration (MVR)

zyMvrMaxNumberOfVlans.name: zyMvrMaxNumberOfVlans
zyMvrMaxNumberOfVlans.description: The maximum number of multicast VLAN registration (MVR) VLAN entries that can be created.

zyxelMvrTable.name: zyxelMvrTable
zyxelMvrTable.description: The table contains multicast VLAN registration (MVR) configuration.

zyxelMvrEntry.name: zyxelMvrEntry
zyxelMvrEntry.description: An entry contains multicast VLAN registration (MVR) configuration.

zyMvrVid.name: zyMvrVid
zyMvrVid.description: Enter the VLAN ID (1 to 4094) of the multicast VLAN.

zyMvrName.name: zyMvrName
zyMvrName.description: Enter a descriptive name (up to 32 printable ASCII characters) for identification purposes.

zyMvrMode.name: zyMvrMode
zyMvrMode.description: Specify the MVR mode on the Switch. Choices are Dynamic and Compatible. Select Dynamic to send IGMP reports to all MVR source ports in the multicast VLAN. Select Compatible to set the Switch not to send IGMP reports.

zyMvr8021pPriority.name: zyMvr8021pPriority
zyMvr8021pPriority.description: Select a priority level (0-7) with which the Switch replaces the priority in outgoing IGMP control packets (belonging to this multicast VLAN).

zyMvrRowStatus.name: zyMvrRowStatus
zyMvrRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted from the Multicast VLAN Registration (MVR) table.

zyxelMvrPortTable.name: zyxelMvrPortTable
zyxelMvrPortTable.description: The table contains multicast VLAN registration (MVR) port configuration.

zyxelMvrPortEntry.name: zyxelMvrPortEntry
zyxelMvrPortEntry.description: An entry contains multicast VLAN registration (MVR) port configuration.

zyMvrPortRole.name: zyMvrPortRole
zyMvrPortRole.description: Specify the roles on the port. None(1), Set the port not to participate in MVR. No MVR multicast traffic is sent or received on this port. Source Port(2), Set the port as the MVR source port that sends and receives multicast traffic. All source ports must belong to a single multicast VLAN. Receiver Port(3), Set the port as a receiver port that only receives multicast traffic.

zyMvrPortTagging.name: zyMvrPortTagging
zyMvrPortTagging.description: Enable/Disable this port to tag the VLAN ID on all the outgoing frames.

zyMvrMaxNumberOfGroups.name: zyMvrMaxNumberOfGroups
zyMvrMaxNumberOfGroups.description: The maximum number of Multicast VLAN Registration (MVR) groups that can be created.

zyxelMvrGroupTable.name: zyxelMvrGroupTable
zyxelMvrGroupTable.description: The table contains multicast VLAN registration (MVR) group configuration.

zyxelMvrGroupEntry.name: zyxelMvrGroupEntry
zyxelMvrGroupEntry.description: An entry contains multicast VLAN registration (MVR) group configuration.

zyMvrGroupName.name: zyMvrGroupName
zyMvrGroupName.description: Enter a descriptive name for identification purposes.

zyMvrGroupStartIpAddress.name: zyMvrGroupStartIpAddress
zyMvrGroupStartIpAddress.description: Enter the starting IP multicast address of the multicast group.

zyMvrGroupEndIpAddress.name: zyMvrGroupEndIpAddress
zyMvrGroupEndIpAddress.description: Enter the ending IP multicast address of the multicast group. Enter the same IP address as the Start Address entry if you want to configure only one IP address for a multicast group.

zyMvrGroupRowStatus.name: zyMvrGroupRowStatus
zyMvrGroupRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted from the Multicast VLAN Registration (MVR) group table.
